## git init is basically used wgen u need to initialise git in your project via the terminal
#  git add . basically stages all everything in the project folder
# git commit basically saves a snapshot of the entire folder or project , also git commit -m followed by a tag in quotes makes it easy to know what the updates at that checkpoint is all about
# git push basically pushes the entire project to git hub except for what has been specified in the .gitignore file